item.title: Pattern Depends
item.description: Which is more important, the right to privacy or the right to know? The importance of both depends on your position. â€‹ For example, in a family where we usually think as children, our right to privacy is more important: our parents should not break into our rooms at will, should not look through our cell phones or diaries, and this is the view we have always held.
